  "slug": "sound-machines-sound-piece-v",
  "title": "SOUND MACHINES — SOUND PIECE V",
  "summary": "<p>Yoko Ono's <em>SOUND PIECE V</em> (1996/2024) is newly realized as a digital, on-chain interactive work. Often working in instruction or text-based works, with <em>SOUND PIECE V</em> Ono transforms the traditional musical score into a simple written prompt that elicits everyday sounds — which are, in turn, revealed to be extraordinary: \"Tape the sound of friends laughing together. / Save it for a rainy day.\" Each time the piece is performed, participants can add their recordings, successively building an ever-evolving archive of sound.</p><br><p><em>In honoring the spirit of the piece, Yoko Ono encourages the work to be transferred to each subsequent participant, rather than sold.</em></p>",
  "coverImage": "https://imagedelivery.net/iCRs13uicXIPOWrnuHbaKA/6eb8ef92-d1c7-41e9-b46a-9131abce7400/raw",
